Here is the structured curriculum we will follow:

---

### PHASE 1: DISCOVERY & RESEARCH
* Problem framing and identifying user pain points.
* Conducting user research (interviews, competitive analysis, surveys).
* Creating user personas and empathy maps.

### PHASE 2: STRATEGY & ARCHITECTURE
* Defining user goals using the Jobs-To-Be-Done (JTBD) framework.
* Mapping out user journeys and task flows.
* Building a clean Information Architecture (IA) and sitemap.

### PHASE 3: WIREFRAMING & CONCEPTUALIZATION
* Low-fidelity sketching and ideation (Crazy Eights, paper wireframes).
* Mid-fidelity wireframes focusing entirely on UX, hierarchy, and layout (no colors or fonts yet).
* Establishing user testing protocols for wireframes.

### PHASE 4: VISUAL DESIGN & SYSTEMIZATION (UI)
* Defining the visual identity (mood boards, typography, color theory).
* Adopting a modern, minimal, and highly professional editorial layout.
* Building a scalable, reusable design system (components, variants, auto-layout tokens).

### PHASE 5: PROTOTYPING & INTERACTION DESIGN
* Creating high-fidelity, interactive prototypes with realistic transitions.
* Micro-interactions, motion design, and state changes (hover, active, loading).

### PHASE 6: VALIDATION & HANDOFF
* Usability testing methods and analyzing feedback loops.
* Design handoff preparation (specifications, asset exporting, dev-readiness).

